  <description><![CDATA[<p>The NH Collection Taormina sits on the hillside just outside the centre of the beautiful old town on Sicily’s eastern coastline. The 20th century building retains many of its original features but has been brought into the 21st century with vibrant modern touches. Just a short walk from the hotel is the pedestrianised lively main shopping street, Corso Umberto that meanders through the heart of the historic town, ending at the Piazza Duomo. You are just minutes away from the crystal-clear shores of Taormina Mare.</p>
<p>The hotel's roof terrace is positioned high above the rooftops, offering panoramic views that look out over <a data-udi="umb://document/919b72992bd64fd4a35a60df994feff6" href="/{localLink:umb://document/919b72992bd64fd4a35a60df994feff6}" title="Taormina Area">Taormina</a> and the Bay of Naxos. Relax on the terrace by the pool whilst sipping a cocktail from the Infinity bar. Or, if you are really in the mood to unwind, head to the hotel SPA for a sauna, steam bath or treatment. Rest in the hotel’s luxurious and modern bedrooms, decorated with warm earthy tones, that create the perfect comfortable environment after a day of taking in Sicily’s wonderful sights.</p>
<p>The hotel boasts two excellent restaurants that serve local Sicilian cuisine. If you fancy something light, head over to the Lu Souli Bar and Restaurant, where chef Natalie Gunta will serve up fresh and tasty local dishes. For your evening meal the Zafiro Restaurant is the place to be, sat on the rooftop and admiring the stunning views. With the region's finest local ingredients, the chef creates delicious combinations of Sicilian gastronomy that are sure to satisfy all your senses.</p>
<p>Transfer time: approx. 1 hour by private car from Catania Airport </p>]]></description>
