  <facilityDescription><![CDATA[<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Restaurants &amp; Bars</strong></span></p>
<p><strong>Zefiro Restaurant </strong>is open during the summer months. It's housed on the 7th floor of the hotel and offers magical views - on a clear day Mount Etna can be seen. The restaurant serves local Sicilian cuisine created using the finest local ingredients. The chef is known for creating delicious combinations that satisfy all of the senses. Open Monday to Sunday 7:30pm - 12am</p>
<p>During the winter months the restaurant is found on the second floor in an elegant indoor setting with the same offer of cuisine. Open Monday to Sunday 7:30pm - 10:30pm. </p>
<p><strong>Lu Souli Bar and Restaurant </strong>offers an ideal place to marvel at ancient Greek theater of Taormina, whilst sampling the delicious light lunch produced  chef Natale Gunta produces. The chef is renowned for her contemporary twist on traditional recipes. </p>
<p><strong>Poolside Infinity bar</strong> where you can order drinks and snacks. </p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Pool</strong></span></p>
<ul>
<li>Outdoor swimming pool and sun terrace with beautiful views across Taormina all the way to the sea. </li>
<li>Pool bar</li>
<li>Lounge chairs and towels available</li>
</ul>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Wellness Centre</strong></span></p>
<ul>
<li>The spa has a sauna, steam bath and offers additional spa treatments (payable at a local rate).</li>
<li>Fitness room with cardio machines and weights. </li>
<li>Swimming pool</li>
</ul>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Practical Facilities </strong></span></p>
<ul>
<li>Free wifi</li>
</ul>]]></facilityDescription>
